Africa's lumber producers will convene in Angola to discuss new policies for imports and exports.
The African Timber Organization will host the 17th Africa Timber Conference in Cabinda, focusing on rainforest conservation.
Meanwhile, Malaysia and Austria plan to launch remote sensing satellites to monitor tropical forests.
Yunnan Province in China is also enhancing environmental protection efforts, expanding reserve areas to safeguard endangered species.
Tanzanian Vice-President emphasizes the need for African nations to combat deforestation and desertification.
Overall, concerted efforts are crucial to preserve the rich biodiversity of these vital ecosystems.
